name: Amy Friend, Guest Quilter
description: Amy Friend is a designer, quilter and sewer. She earned her B.A. and completed her M.A. coursework in Art History. After working as a collections curator, she decided to stay home and raise her three children. For a creative outlet, Amy turned to sewing and blogging. From there, she worked with BasicGrey to create quilt designs, with Art Gallery Fabrics as a member of their Fat Quarter Gang, as a project designer for Therm O Web, and design team member for Sizzix. She enjoys sewing, especially projects that are complex and challenging. She also likes paper piecing and precise patchwork designs. If Amy is not sewing or caring for her family, she's likely gardening at her home in West Newbury, Mass.

name: Angela Southey, Sizzix
description: Angela has always enjoyed working with textiles and yarn. She learned to sew, knit, crochet, macramé and lace while she was still a teenager. A career in teaching textiles was an obvious choice, until she chose to run her own business as a designer and seamstress while raising her family. Later, she began working for a shop specializing in fabrics for patchwork where a new interest and hobby was born. Since then, Angela has become manager of the shop and appears at patchwork shows, helping with the new fabric range. Angela joined Sizzix in 2012 as a member of the design team creating projects and quilts with the newest dies. She can't wait to share her creativity with you!

name: Betsy Kaage, Vintaj
description: Betsy and her husband, Bill, happily raise their two children in the lush landscape of Galena, Illinois. Always seeking ways to live a creative life, Betsy jumped at the chance to paint, sew, knead, link, wrap and rivet for her friends at Vintaj. She uses all of the artistic skills learned from her previous careers in theatre and textile design and enjoys adding more to her repertoire. Her inspiration comes from nature, history and clever, funny people. Betsy appreciates her job flexibility and the opportunities available while living in a small country town.

name: Brenda Walton
description: Brenda's world travels have greatly influenced her classic, nature-inspired designs, which have been warming hearts for over 20 years. Her artistic career began with a passion for sophisticated calligraphy, watercolor painting and graphic design. Her elegant work has been translated into an extensive array of popular, licensed products, including scrapbooking collections for K&Company and greeting card and gift collections for Papyrus. Brenda brings her graceful hand lettering, illustration and vintage imagery to a distinctive line of charming and sophisticated dies for Sizzix. Brenda's die cutting and embossing products make it easy for crafters to express themselves artfully, to create unique personalized gifts and to celebrate each and every day. Learn more about Brenda Walton.

name: Cara Mariano, Sizzix
description:
Cara has been scrapbooking for more than 10 years and currently spends her days working as Art Director for Ellison. She enjoys spending time with her husband, Glenn, and taking pictures. Cara also loves going to the beach, which she is able to do quite often since she lives in warm and sunny Southern California.

When she's not relaxing on the beach, her free time is spent scrapbooking. She describes her scrapbooking style as clean and simple, with the focus on the pictures. She has a passion for pink cardstock, and her favorite scrapbooking subjects are her friends and family.

name: Cheryl Adam, Guest Quilter
description: Trained in architectural engineering, Cheryl started quilting as a hobby in 1982 and eight years later turned her passion into a profession. Leveraging her educational background, she enjoys designing her own quilts and drafting the patterns, and her work has been featured in some of the hobby's most prestigious publications. In 2003, her experiences culminated with her insightful book Off Center Patchwork. In addition to having served as the technical editor for McCall's Vintage Quilts Magazine, Cheryl has also taught local quilting classes and exhibits her quilts at many shows and events.

name: Cindy Surina, Guest Quilter
description: Some may know Cindy as the quilter/owner of Custom Creations or as a vendor at many large retail quilt shows with her rainbow table of "Fat Quarter Queen" fabrics. She became addicted to appliqué in the early 1980s and searched everywhere for fun and unique machine appliqué designs. After years of selling her products at area boutiques and bazaars, she taught machine appliqué classes at many locations throughout Southern California, primarily at The Fabric Patch in Upland. By 1995, she was designing and wholesaling patterns under the Custom Creations label. Her current focus on retail shows has been rewarded with a loyal customer base.

name: Debi Potter, Sizzix
description:
Debi has been papercrafting for more than 10 years and currently spends her days working as a freelance designer creating inspirational projects for the consumer craft magazines in the UK. More recently, Debi has turned her attention to working with fabric to create stylish home décor projects and describes her style as shabby chic using florals, stripes and polka dots.

When she's not tending to magazine submissions, Debi runs workshops at craft shops and consumer craft fairs. This allows her to share ideas and spend time with fellow crafters.

name: Deena Ziegler, Sizzix
description: Deena has always stored memorabilia in albums but has been "officially" scrapbooking for more than 15 years now. Her favorite scrapbooking subjects are her daughters, Niguel and Kylah, and she will always set aside time to scrapbook when they are willing to join her. Deena and her husband, Randy, have also collected many travel photos through the years, which she enjoys scrapbooking. Deena has a love of cardmaking and teaches card classes at stores and online. When Deena's not scrapbooking her personal memories, she's here at Sizzix helping to inspire you with new techniques and creative ways to use your die-cuts.

name: Janette Daneshmand, Sizzix
description: Janette is a craft designer, snailmail artist and author of the Janette Lane blog. She's also the creator of Pocket Letters™, an artful way to send pen pal letters around the world. Janette has been crafting her whole life, but more so since discovering the world of papercrafting via social media. She was born and raised in Orange County, Calif. and continues to reside there in the city of Fullerton with her wonderful husband, Justin. Janette also enjoys making her planner and Pocket Letter-related YouTube videos and thrifting! She's inspired by her faith and the world around her, and always tries to look for humor and beauty in everyday life.

name: Jeanne Holland, Vintaj
description: Jeanne's design career started early on when her grandmother gave her a box of antique glass beads and broken necklaces. Captivated immediately, she continued to design through high school, occasionally selling her creations. Her love of form and function and pursuit of a career that allowed for family lead her to Brigham Young University. There she expressed herself in everything from classical ballet to stained glass mosaic. Jeanne went on to own an art and jewelry shop in Galena, Illinois, and, along with her sister Wendy, formed the Vintaj Design Studios and eventually, the Vintaj Natural Bass Co.

name: Jess Italia-Lincoln, Vintaj
description: Her design influence is far reaching. As the educator for Vintaj, Jess teaches and shares many tips and techniques in online videos and Vintaj Jewelry Technique Books. Inspired by nature and all its treasures, Jess started her creative career odyssey by graduating with a bachelor's degree in advertising design at the International Academy of Merchandising & Design in Chicago. In the fast-paced city, she always made time for designing handmade clothing, purses and quilts. However, vintage fabrics gave way to beads which lead her to discover her true passion - jewelry design. Jess relocated to the beauty and history of Galena, Illinois, which continues to inspire her designs, while keeping her strongly connected with family.

name: Jill MacKay
description: Inspired by the patterns and forms of nature, Jill MacKay is an accomplished jewelry designer, sculptor, teacher, author and consultant. Her enthusiasm and 25 years of creative experience make her one of the most skilled, diversified and sought-after artists today. The Jill MacKay brand continues to evolve and charm, selling in over 2000 stores internationally, on television and online. Among her accomplishments, Jill has designed for the soap opera, Guiding Light, and Star Trek: The Next Generation. As a writer, she regularly contributes designs and educational content to prominent book and magazine publishers. Jill has been nationally recognized for helping those less fortunate and solving social issues through the arts. Jill lives and works from her studios in Bellvue, Colorado.

name: Jo Packham
description: Jo Packham is all about creative expression. Whether it's food, art or business, the creator/Editor-in-Chief of popular magazine titles such as Where Women Create, Where Women Cook, and Where Women Create Business has been a leading innovator in the handmade publishing market for more than 30 years. In 2013, the Ogden, Utah resident became a licensed designer for Sizzix. Her line of die-cutting and embossing products are inspired from the pages of her Where Women Cook and Where Women Create magazines with designs to add unique flavor to cards, labels, décor, party favors and more.

name: Jorli Perine
description: Jorli can't remember a time when she wasn't drawing or painting. By age 5, she was sketching recognizable portraits. Her official training began as the recipient of the Laguna Beach Festival of the Arts scholarship, and continued with her art education at Brigham Young University and Laguna College of Art and Design. Her mother, LaDorna Eichenberg, the founder of Ellison Educational Equipment, involved Jorli in the business from the beginning by having her cut out pink felt bunnies and send them to teachers. Throughout the years, Jorli has filled many company roles. Her artwork launched the first 2000 Ellison Educational dies. She still designs for Ellison, Sizzix and the quilting segment of the business, while pursuing her fine arts career.

name: Karen Burniston
description: Karen Burniston is a well-known designer and papercrafter who focuses primarily on designing pop-up and interactive techniques. She has been published in all the major papercraft magazines and has contributed to numerous idea books. She teaches pop-up classes at stores and events throughout the world. Her family consists of John, a fellow engineer, twin children, Karl and Emma, and two high-maintenance Puggles. Learn more about Karen and find links to video tutorials for her Sizzix pop-up dies on her blog: I am not left-handed.

name: Kathleen Bahret, Guest Quilter
description:
Kathleen's love of needlework began at age 10 when her paternal grandmother taught her embroidery. From there, Kathleen's love of threads grew to include needlepoint, quilting, embroidery and counted cross stitch. Her art background helps her put a little of her own design into most projects.

Kathleen was born in St. Louis, Miss., relocated to California in middle school and has lived there ever since. She has two daughters, four grandkids and one beloved dog. Happily married for over 50 years, the Bahrets are now retired. When travel plans are made, the needle and threads are the first things packed!

name: Kathy Ranabargar, Sizzix
description:
Kathy has always been fascinated by fabrics. She loves to touch them, look at them and imagine what she can do with them. She has been sewing almost all her life; Kathy's mother taught her the basics and, while dating her husband, she learned quilting from her mother-in-law. Her inspirations are her garden and the ocean and her influences include her experiences in fashion and theater costuming.

Born and raised in Temple City, Calif., Kathy now lives in Laguna Beach, Calif., with her husband, two teenage boys and two black labs.

name: Kerry Goulder
description: Kerry Goulder has been sewing for fun since she can remember. After a sculpture class in college, a wedding and two children, Kerry began designing many unique patterns under her Kid Giddy® label, and wrote her first book, Sewing Tales to Stitch and Love: 18 Toy Patterns for the Storytelling Sewist, with F+W Media. Kerry's company motto is to "add more giddy to your life." This is a constant reminder to have fun and to do things that make you happy, which, of course, means more sewing. Kerry lives in Southern Maine with her husband and their two daughters. When she's not sewing, she loves to run and is training for her second degree black belt in Shaolin Kempo Karate.

name: Linda Nitzen, Sizzix
description: Learning from her mother how to embroider, crochet and sew at age 7, Linda realized her love of blankets and quilts on a family vacation during high school. Not only were two wool blankets the only treasures she brought home from that trip, but she followed that up by making her first quilt. Self-taught, it would be 10 years before she took her first class, and from there it's been non-stop fun growing her skills and learning new techniques. A native Southern Californian, she's been happily married to her husband for 22 years and together they have two terrific teenage boys. "My boys learned early on," jokes Linda, "that if Mom gets to quilt each day, the house is much happier.""

name: Mackenzie Mullane, Vintaj
description: It didn't take Mackie long to pick up handfuls of her mom's stones and filigrees and begin creating settings. After all, mom (Wendy Mullane) would often joke that Mackie bathed in jewels! Designing since she could first hold tools, Mackie has been selling her designs in shops and at art fairs ever since. With this unlimited imagination, she has been a youthful asset to the Vintaj design team. Her designs have been published in several books which helped her connect with aspiring jewelry designers. She has a great appreciation for art in all forms and is truly fascinated with creative expression!

name: Mou Saha
description: Born in Calcutta, India, Mou loves to design and share her handmade art. Her creative journey began in 2004 when she saw a scrapbooking TV show and made a baby book for her 2-year-old daughter. At the urging of impressed friends, she submitted her work to magazines and applied for design team positions. Eventually, she became a contributing writer for Creating Keepsakes Magazine. Over the years, she has designed for Tim Holtz, Anna Griffin, Big Picture Classes, Faber-Castell, Glitz Design, October Afternoon, Crate Paper and more. She describes her style as experimental and loves everything from mixed media to mini books. In her spare time, Mou enjoys her family, living in Florida, movies, spicy food, flea markets and art journals!

name: Paula Pascual, Sizzix
description: As a teenager in her native Spain, Paula ambitiously made cards and crafts. Starting in 2003, her experience grew as a craft store demonstrator and as a freelance creative designer/tutor. Not long after, Paula began using Sizzix products in her workshops and demonstrations. Over the last six years, Paula has been featured in popular publications such as Cardmaking and Papercraft and Crafts Beautiful. She has also authored two craft books: Creative Card Making and Handmade Celtic Cards. In addition, she has appeared several times on QVC as their craft expert. Paula enjoys working with paper, graphic design, photography and storage, which inspired her to create the Crafty Storage, a collaborative blog dedicated to storage ideas from and for all crafters.

name: Pete Hughes, Sizzix
description:
Sizzix designer Pete lives in the picturesque town of Llangollen in North Wales with his wife and two children. In his spare time, Pete helps out at his local karate club, plays and collects electric guitars and follows his beloved Liverpool Football Club.

For over ten years, Pete has been inspiring UK and European crafters with his amazing ideas. After leaving school, Pete trained as an illustrator, specializing in cartoons and caricatures before taking up a position for an educational publishing company. Pete has worked for Ellison since 2005, where he enjoys producing projects for UK and European magazines, trade shows and demonstrations. Pete is also featured regularly on television demonstrating Sizzix products, most recently on QVC.

name: Ronda McCord, Guest Quilter
description: Ronda McCord has always enjoyed all forms of sewing and crafting but quilting is her true passion. With more than 20 years of quilting experience, she continues to challenge herself with exciting new ways to express her creativity. Ronda particularly enjoys piecing together quilt tops. She likes using Sizzix dies in her projects to easily accomplish perfect points and seams. In addition, she loves making and giving baby quilts to family and friends for their new bundles of joy. She and her husband have been married for 31 years and reside in sunny southern California. They have one son, three daughters and two grandsons.

name: Shirley Van Dyken, Guest Quilter
description: Shirley began her creative journey by taking up sewing at a very young age. That led to a love of quilting beginning in the mid-1970s. Her career shaping influences include working in bridal alterations and gaining the invaluable experience of working in a quilt shop for almost 15 years. In addition to being involved in five different quilt guilds, Shirley currently performs commission work and always makes time for her passion, machine quilting. She and her husband, Jim, live in Southwest Colorado where together they own a restaurant. They have four children between them and four grandchildren.

name: Stacey Rogers, Sizzix
description:
Sizzix Designer Stacey Rogers has been designing characters and making cards since leaving college. Stacey trained as an Illustrator at University and also recently qualified as a teacher of Art & Design. In her Illustration work and card making Stacey loves to use inks and enjoys finding new methods of applying them to create different effects.

Stacey joined Sizzix in November 2009 and enjoys producing projects for UK magazines and craft shows.

name: Stacy Surina-Bonora, Guest Quilter
description: A certifiable arts & crafts junkie, Stacy loves anything creative. She's been scrapbooking since her teen years. As the owner of Purls & Girls, a Central California yarn shoppe, she taught knitting and crochet to the new wave of hobbyists with exciting designs, materials and colors. Stacy has become an integral part of the success the Custom Creations label enjoys, working in design and production. An accomplished home chef, Stacy enjoys entertaining friends and family at home, where her husband and two children enjoy her cooking and knack for design whether she is making party invitations, wrapping presents or decorating the trailer for a "Glamping Trip!"

name: Stephanie Ackerman
description: Whether it's paper, fabric, dough or paint, Stephanie Ackerman is a mixed media artist and teacher who's a lot like you, combining a busy mom lifestyle with her many creative passions. Stephanie draws upon her vast experiences in stamp carving, stitching, art journaling, making tags and working with canvas and wood to inspire this uniquely upbeat collection just for you! Learn more about Stephanie by visiting her website: StephanieAckermanDesigns.com.

name: Susan Tierney-Cockburn
description: Susan has taken a lifetime of creative experiences and turned them into a full-time passion. Whether it's gardening, painting, baking, and, of course, crafting, she has done it all in her own unmistakable style. Loving to share this information with others, she has taught cake decorating and bread baking. Her stamping and papercrafts - with a special emphasis on making realistic paper flowers - have lead to designing for publications and writing books. In addition, she has a blog dedicated to baking. Susan teams with Sizzix for a charming crop of products to create incredible floral designs for embellishing cards, scrapbooks or any other craft project.

name: Tammy Tutterow
description: A lifelong artist and crafter, Tammy grew up in a home full of arts & crafts with very creative parents. Her true crafting passion comes from papercrafts, ribbonwork and sewing as she strives to use all three together in her projects. Tammy has also been an instructor and project designer in the papercraft/scrapbook industry for over 6 years. She has worked with many top manufacturers including Sizzix, Tim Holtz, Ranger Ink, BasicGrey, Pink Paislee and Therm O Web. She has contributed to several books, magazines, catalogs and TV appearances. Her classes are offered at stores, conventions and online.

name: Tim Holtz
description: Tim Holtz is the Creative Director for Ranger Industries, one of the leading manufacturers of innovative inks, paints and embossing products. Tim plays an integral part in the development and design of cutting-edge papercrafting products. Tim has teamed up with various key companies like Ranger, Advantus, Tonic Studios, Sizzix and Stampers Anonymous to bring unique products that work hand in hand with Ranger's extensive lines. Learn more about Tim and connect to video tutorials and his blog at TimHoltz.com.

name: Victoria Findlay Wolfe
description: Whether it's painting, sculpting or photography, Victoria has always been creating. But it was through her grandmother, Elda Wolfe, a "crazy quilter" whose patterns were ahead of their time, that she found the inspiration to take up quilting. Victoria's series of Double Wedding Ring quilts are based on happy childhood memories with her grandparents. Victoria is also a teacher, lecturer, fabric and thread designer, blogger and author of the popular quilting books, 15 Minutes of Play and Double Wedding Rings - Traditions Made Modern. Victoria finds that making and giving quilts in her community quilt program, along with her loving family, to be her greatest joys in life.

name: Wendy Cuskey, Sizzix
description: Having worked in the legal field for over 20 years, Wendy Cuskey knows the daily grind of the 9-5 world all too well. As a member of the Sizzix design team, Wendy gets to unleash her eclectic style and inspiring view of creativity onto many different mediums, including her favorite means to express herself, paper. Wendy first started scrapbooking with pictures of her children and has been papercrafting ever since with her family and everyday life as her inspirations. She enjoys creating mini albums as unique gifts and to showcase summer beach days and the vacations she enjoys with her husband, two boys and her yorkie who all reside happily in sunny southern California.

name: Wendy Mullane, Vintaj
description: A tomboy while growing up, Wendy preferred mud to beads. Once college bound, she pursued art and design at Brigham Young University. She combined this passion for art with her love of nostalgia by opening an antique and jewelry shop in 1991, while raising her four children. For 10 years, Wendy worked with metals and broke through creatively when she and her sister Jeanne discovered the creative filigree settings technique. With this unique innovation, she formed Vintaj Design Studios and eventually co-founded Vintaj Natural Brass Co. Her life experiences have prepared her well to serve as President of this amazing company.

name: 2015 VBS - Camp Discovery
description: It's no secret that Vacation Bible School themes are essential to lesson planning and related activities. Ellison die-cutting equipment helps easily create many exciting shapes to support this year's VBS themes. Imagine designing your own meaningful visuals, projects, games, room décor and more to unlock basic and advanced faith-based concepts. With Ellison, you can!

name: Ellison Machines & Accessories
description: Whether you're reinforcing lessons, promoting hands-on activities or just decorating your next themed bulletin board, Ellison shape-cutting machines create the perfect applications to meet your important standards. Ideal for the classroom and home school environments, our machines are easy-to-operate and cut many different materials for countless curriculum-based shapes. Use them to enhance any subject, while increasing retention and making learning fun!

name: Ellison Shape-Cutting
description: When it comes to cutting your own curriculum based-shapes with our machines, you have many choices. That's because we offer many dies and cartridges featuring versatile images for countless lesson applications. To view them, you can refine your search in the left hand column by subcategories, themes, curriculum and more.

name: Ellison Supplies
description: They're the perfect products to complement your Ellison shape-cutting equipment. Our Supplies offer an added element of creativity to powerfully present your cut-out shapes. Stock up on these useful items today you never know when they'll be gone for good!

name: Products-to-Project Kits
description: Don't just sell Sizzix products … Show your customers exactly what kinds of projects can be created. The Products-to-Projects Kit not only enhances product visibility, but also increases product turns and demand. Create your own class by using our project or create your own.

name: Sizzix Embossing
description:
A handmade Mother's Day card. Embossed party invites with your unique touch. Gift tags for your child's teachers. For every moment in your life, Sizzix offers a shape that perfectly matches the sentiment.

Compatible with a wide range of materials, our current selection of essential creative products includes everything you need to emboss and add texture when using your Sizzix machine.

name: Sizzix Machines & Accessories
description: From wedding invitations and decorations to making memories of your last vacation last a little longer, Sizzix die-cutting, electronic shape-cutting and embossing machines truly empower your creativity.Our growing family of award-winning Sizzix machines are available in different sizes, options and capabilities to fit any size imagination. For more information, watch this video: Choosing Your Sizzix Machine.

name: Sizzix Media
description: Connecting the story behind your most treasured creations, TalkingTag Labels literally lend a recorded voice to any fabric project. After downloading a free TalkingTag app to any smart phone, simply scan the tag and record up to one minute of personalized audio. (For playback, scan the tag again from any smart phone and retrieve the voice recording from a secured platform.) Attach the tag and hear your creation come to life!

name: Sizzix Merchandise
description: We now have an ever-growing range of Sizzix branded merchandise available on Sizzix.co.uk including crafting essentials and other accessories.

name: Sizzix Shape-Cutting
description:
A handmade card. Fabric accents for a striking fashion statement. Gift tags for your child's teachers. For every moment in your life, Sizzix offers a shape that perfectly matches the sentiment.

Compatible with a wide range of materials, our current selection of essential creative products includes everything you need to die-cut when using your Sizzix machine.

name: Sizzix Supplies
description: They're the perfect products to complement your shape-cutting equipment. Our Supplies offer an added element of creativity to powerfully present your cut-out shapes. Stock up on these useful items today - you never know when they'll be gone for good!

name: Sizzix Gift Cards
description:
Looking for a useful gift idea? Gift cards more than fit the bill! Ideal for birthdays, holidays and teacher appreciation, a Sizzix/Ellison Gift Card can be applied toward product purchases at either Sizzix.com or EllisonEducation.com. Sizzix eshape Store Gift Cards can be applied toward product purchases at the Sizzix eshape Store. This added flexibility allows the recipient more creative choices than ever!

Please note: Gift cards are shipped free of charge via USPS Priority Mail and must be purchased separately from any other order for merchandise. At this time, gift cards can only be shipped to addresses in the United States, including APO/FPO.

name: English Language Arts
description: Ellison loves Language Arts. That's why we offer so many curriculum-based dies featuring this subject, including popular alphabets and designs to create essential hands-on activities and engaging visuals. Each shape reinforces core concepts such as reading, writing, spelling and grammar, while promoting interactive fun for today's creative classroom. Ellison Dies are supported by free lessons to download or print out for amazing activities all year long!

name: STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering & Math)
description: Ellison loves STEM. That's why we offer so many curriculum-based dies featuring science, technology, engineering and math to create essential hands-on activities and engaging visuals. Each shape reinforces core concepts, while promoting interactive fun for today's creative classroom.

name: 7gypsies
description: So who exactly are the 7gypsies? Established in 2000, 7gypsies is the invention of an amazing married couple with an eye for art, collecting and creating for their family. Named in honor of their 7 beautiful children, the couple came up with a business venture that combines their vast traveling experiences with their passion for designing for the scrapbooking industry. They roam the craft and scrapbooking industries, looking for the whimsical, the faded and worn, the fantastic and beautiful little objects others leave behind. These are the treasures that bring stories to life. Now they've teamed up with Sizzix on a collection of designs to bring you closer to your own personal creative odyssey! Learn more about 7gypsies.

name: BasicGrey
description: Deliciously different. Ambitiously diverse. Remarkably distinct. That's BasicGrey. BasicGrey is an award-winning, US-based design house which creates self-branded and licensed products for the scrapbooking, fabric and general craft industries. This multi-disciplined team also creates digital content that can be transformed into digital scrapbooks, blogs and e-cards. Originality is the backbone of every BasicGrey design, as well as for every product manufactured and every approach to a new project. BasicGrey strives to set the standard and not follow the trend. This hobby innovator sees themselves as the bar to be measured by and the company to watch because of their one-of-a-kind qualities. BasicGrey remains true to its popular avant-garde style, offering artists exceptional designs and products.

name: Beth Reames
description: In her 16-plus years in the scrapbooking industry, Beth has lost count of the idea books and magazines to which she has contributed. She worked as a product designer for EK Success for eight years, partnered with a friend to create the Border Buddy template line and worked with Ellison for eight years as a craft designer. Beth and her husband, Randy, have four children and find that the kids and their friends provide plenty of scrapbooking photo ops. Beth says the worst thing about scrapbooking is when the time comes to clean off her desk!

name: Brenda Pinnick
description: Brenda Pinnick is an artist and a designer who combines her natural talent, her professional skills and her love of color to create delightful art for products including Sizzix dies, fabric for Henry Glass, stationery products for a number of clients and for home goods. Brenda is well known by crafters the world over for her playful art offered as crafting products sold in stores, on television and on the internet. Her fans enjoy learning techniques and being inspired by her creativity, her passion and her expertise as she shares her multi-disciplined knowledge with crafters and artisans alike. Brenda is a dynamic and generous teacher who inspires her students to find the artist within. Visit Brenda Pinnick.com to learn more!

name: Brenda Walton
description: Brenda's world travels have greatly influenced her classic, nature-inspired designs, which have been warming hearts for over 20 years. Her artistic career began with a passion for sophisticated calligraphy, watercolor painting and graphic design. Her elegant work has been translated into an extensive array of popular, licensed products, including scrapbooking collections for K&Company and greeting card and gift collections for Papyrus. Brenda brings her graceful hand lettering, illustration and vintage imagery to a distinctive line of charming and sophisticated dies for Sizzix. Brenda's die cutting and embossing products make it easy for crafters to express themselves artfully, to create unique personalized gifts and to celebrate each and every day. Learn more about Brenda Walton.

name: Build-A-Bear Workshop
description: You've got a style of your own. And so does Build-A-Bear Workshop®. Check out all their latest and greatest die and embossing folder designs shown below. Just imagine the kinds of things you could create with these designs. Then wonder how you lived without them this long.

name: Cara Mariano
description:
Cara has been scrapbooking for more than 10 years and currently spends her days working as Art Director for Ellison. She enjoys spending time with her husband, Glenn, and taking pictures. Cara also loves going to the beach, which she is able to do quite often since she lives in warm and sunny Southern California.

When she's not relaxing on the beach, her free time is spent scrapbooking. She describes her scrapbooking style as clean and simple, with the focus on the pictures. She has a passion for pink cardstock, and her favorite scrapbooking subjects are her friends and family.

name: Classroom Series
description: Class is now in session for the Sizzix Classroom Series. This must-have collection of Sizzix Dies and eclips cartridges boldly creates a multitude of engaging shapes to empower learning in the classroom and beyond. Ideal for any teacher, tutor or parent motivating students to succeed, each shape enhances creative arts & crafts as well as many other subject areas to make every discovery amazing!

name: Craft Asylum
description: Craft Asylum® launched in 2014 and provides the perfect community for any creative ability, offering crafters quality products that are individually designed to work in harmony. They embrace each and every crafter to make timeless masterpieces that can be shared with friends and family. Time is one of the most important gifts and Craft Asylum supports this ethos through their inspiring product categories that are forever growing. Featuring gorgeous coordinating collections of papers, stamps and embellishments, plus an exciting collaboration with Sizzix®, there is plenty in store for fans of this fresh new brand!

name: Debi Adams
description:
Debi is no stranger to the scrapbooking industry; she's been scrapbooking for more than 15 years and has designed a variety of embellishments and dies. Debi worked with Ellison for eight years as a craft designer. She enjoys sewing unique fashion and home décor items, as well as creating custom wall murals. Her "addictions" include Saturday morning garage sales and window shopping at Anthropologie.

Debi has four daughters, Kristen, Chellie, Lauren and Alyssa. They enjoy water sports, dancing and planning unique themed holidays for their family get togethers.

name: Debi Potter
description:
Debi has been papercrafting for more than 10 years and currently spends her days working as a freelance designer creating inspirational projects for the consumer craft magazines in the UK. More recently, Debi has turned her attention to working with fabric to create stylish home décor projects and describes her style as shabby chic using florals, stripes and polka dots.

When she's not tending to magazine submissions, Debi runs workshops at craft shops and consumer craft fairs. This allows her to share ideas and spend time with fellow crafters.

name: Deena Rutter
description: You've got a style of your own. And so does Deena Rutter. Check out her die and embossing folder designs shown below. Just imagine the kinds of things you could create with these designs. Then wonder how you lived without them this long.

name: Deena Ziegler
description: Deena has always stored memorabilia in albums but has been "officially" scrapbooking for more than 15 years now. Her favorite scrapbooking subjects are her daughters, Niguel and Kylah, and she will always set aside time to scrapbook when they are willing to join her. Deena and her husband, Randy, have also collected many travel photos through the years, which she enjoys scrapbooking. Deena has a love of cardmaking and teaches monthly card classes at a local store and online. When Deena's not scrapbooking her personal memories, she's here at Sizzix helping to inspire you with new techniques and creative ways to use your die-cuts.

name: Dena Designs
description: "Embellish your life" is Dena's motto, and her products, books and media exposure have reached a legion of fans that value friendship, home, family and self-expression. As President and Creative Director of Dena Designs, Inc., Dena has beautifully juggled the roles of designer, businesswoman and mom while crafting a hugely successful company, lifestyle brand and wide array of products, ranging from home décor and accessories to greeting cards, gifts, craft items, books and more. What began 20 years ago as a Bloomingdale's best-selling bedding collection is now a merchandising/media program generating multi-millions in worldwide sales. Learn more at Dena Designs.com.

name: doodlebug design inc
description: Known for their impressive variety of creative products for the scrapbook industry, doodlebug design inc. offers everything from paper and stickers to buttons and ribbons - all custom manufactured and color coordinated to match their whimsical product line. Partnering with Sizzix once again for fresh and fun themes, this adorable array of products expresses all the little joys of life. Discover more about doodlebug design inc.

name: Echo Park Paper Co
description: Taking their name from the location of the early Hollywood studios, the Echo Park Paper Company offers a unique, timeless approach to style, form and format. Their paper lines depict a wide range of bright and playful to images with subtle sophistication. Through an exciting partnership, Sizzix transforms some of Echo Park's most popular designs into a dazzling dies. Experience Echo Park.

name: Eileen Hull
description: Eileen grew up in a large family where there was always an art project in the works. She has applied her creative thinking to all sorts of life and career events - from adjusting to thirteen military moves and raising four children to developing product lines for craft manufacturers. In 2009, Sizzix launched her first ScoreBoards™ dies, which are specially designed to cut and score matboard and thicker materials. Eileen enjoys working with recycled materials and "treasures" from thrift stores, or even better, those found on the curb! Eileen resides in Herndon, Virginia with her husband. The couple's newest addition is a vintage camper refurbished as a mobile studio, which she used to travel the country during her 2-month Paper Trail tour.

name: EL Smith
description:
E.L. has been working for Ellison for more than 10 years. Along with her die designing, she also does packaging and graphic design for Ellison.

When not designing dies, she enjoys watercolor painting, gardening and spending time with her grandsons. E.L. has a great love of color, which she uses often in her painting and gardening.

name: Emily Artherton
description: As a Sizzix designer, Emily Atherton finds it exciting to be constantly on the lookout for new trends and influences. With a background in printed textiles and surface pattern, Emily delightfully expands on her experiences to create innovative designs for Sizzix dies and embossing folders. She loves the process of seeing an idea develop from a conceptual sketch on her desk to completion as finished artwork for a die or embossing folder to be enjoyed by other passionate crafters. Emily loves to travel, visit exhibitions and get lost in design journals to feed her inspiration and develop new ideas for her designs.

name: Emily Humble
description: Emily designed for Ellison for more than 5 years. Emily was recently married when she started at Ellison and since then she has had two beautiful girls. She is a graduate of Laguna College of Art and Design where she majored in Illustration. She loves children's books and gets a lot of her inspiration from those illustrations. She loved watching and working with the girls in the art room at Ellison, who gave her lots of inspiration from their creations. While at Ellison, she did what she loved and she loved what she did.

name: French General
description: Bringing the classic look of the rural French countryside to the United States, French General is a vintage craft store/workshop located in Los Angeles, California. Specializing in beads, buttons, millinery and textiles, their French-inspired collection is all about crafting with beautiful textiles and a simple vintage color palette. Having personally combed French flea markets for many of her unique treasures, Kaari Meng, the founder and owner of French General, has designed jewelry for Anthropologie, quilt fabrics for Moda, textiles for Fabricut  and has authored several books, including French-Inspired Jewelry, The French Inspired Home, Handmade Soirees, Treasured Notions and more. Now French General teams up with Sizzix for an exciting collection to organize beads, buttons, needles and notions.

name: Graphic 45
description: Graphic 45 is an award-winning scrapbook and papercrafting company owned and operated by a mother and her two daughters - to help others find their creative voice. The team creates vintage-inspired crafting products that capture the flamboyant style of the 1920s and 30s with vibrant color, irresistible textures and imaginative design. Leveraging this decades-old appeal, Graphic 45 partners with Sizzix to create a forever-stylish collection of products to distinguish any scrapbook page, card or home décor project. Check out Graphic 45.

name: Hampton Art
description: Hampton Art was founded in 1980 by the Gallagher family. For over 20 years, the Gallagher's manufactured premium quality rubber stamps, clear stamps and stamping accessories featuring popular designer lines. The company was sold in 2007 to National Spinning in North Carolina and continues its tradition of creating premium products while expanding the company's offerings with new and exciting partnerships such as the recent collaboration with Sizzix. Learn more about Hampton Art.

name: Heather Lancaster
description: You've got a style of your own. And so does Heather Lancaster. Check out her die designs shown below. Just imagine the kinds of things you could create with these designs. Then wonder how you lived without them this long.

name: Hello Kitty by Sanrio
description: You've got a style of your own. And so does Hello Kitty® by Sanrio®. Check out all her latest and greatest die and embossing folder designs shown below. Just imagine the kinds of things you could create with these designs. Then wonder how you lived without them this long.

name: Hero Arts
description: Hero Arts, a leading design company in the craft industry, began in Jackie Leventhal's Berkeley cottage. Jackie and her young son, Aaron (today the CEO), drew images and made stamps to enliven their letters and cards. With that simple idea, Hero Arts quickly grew into a vital force in the growing stamp movement. Craft fairs gave way to gift shows, and local retail grew into international wholesale distribution. Today, the company is an innovator in the cardmaking and scrapbooking industries, with leading designs and award-winning green business practices. Start to finish, Hero Arts products are made with love and precision, as every product continues to share the simple elegance of Jackie's original vision. Learn more about Hero Arts and connect to their blog at HeroArts.com.

name: Jen Long
description: Jen grew up in Southern California, receiving her B.F.A. from Otis College of Art and Design as well as an M.F.A. in Illustration from California State University, Fullerton (CSUF). An internship followed at Walt Disney Studios based in Character Art at their Consumer Products Division. Her work is a strong combination of both traditional drawing skills and digital technique. Her professional experience includes teaching at the collegiate level for CSUF, digital character art for Disney including the Phineas and Ferb show and professional book illustration. Currently Jen works as a designer for Sizzix.

name: Jill MacKay
description: Inspired by the patterns and forms of nature, Jill MacKay is an accomplished jewelry designer, sculptor, teacher, author and consultant. Her enthusiasm and 25 years of creative experience make her one of the most skilled, diversified and sought-after artists today. The Jill MacKay brand continues to evolve and charm, selling in over 2000 stores internationally, on television and online. Among her accomplishments, Jill has designed for the soap opera, Guiding Light, and Star Trek: The Next Generation. As a writer, she regularly contributes designs and educational content to prominent book and magazine publishers. Jill has been nationally recognized for helping those less fortunate and solving social issues through the arts. Jill lives and works from her studios in Bellvue, Colorado.

name: Jillibean Soup
description: Specializing in fresh, innovative and high-quality products for the paper crafting industry, Jillibean Soup products are manufactured with close attention to color, detail and design. This inspiring company prides itself in finding the best ingredients to create fun designs that whimsically suit any taste or time. Joining forces with Hampton Art, Inc., a leading stamp and stamp accessory manufacturer for over 20 years, Jillibean Soup has utilize this talented staff to market, manufacture, and distribute its unforgettable products. With its releases for Sizzix, Jillibean Soup continues to cook up a delicious blend of style and versatility for your next card, scrapbook page and more. Discover more about Jillibean Soup.

name: Jorli Perine
description: Jorli can't remember a time when she wasn't drawing or painting. By age 5, she was sketching recognizable portraits. Her official training began as the recipient of the Laguna Beach Festival of the Arts scholarship, and continued with her art education at Brigham Young University and Laguna College of Art and Design. Her mother, LaDorna Eichenberg, the founder of Ellison Educational Equipment, involved Jorli in the business from the beginning by having her cut out pink felt bunnies and send them to teachers. Throughout the years, Jorli has filled many company roles. Her artwork launched the first 2000 Ellison Educational dies. She still designs for Ellison, Sizzix and the quilting segment of the business, while pursuing her fine arts career.

name: Karen Burniston
description: Karen Burniston is a well-known designer and papercrafter who focuses primarily on designing pop-up and interactive techniques. She has been published in all the major papercraft magazines and has contributed to numerous idea books. She teaches pop-up classes at stores and events throughout the world. Her family consists of John, a fellow engineer, twin children, Karl and Emma, and two high-maintenance Puggles. Learn more about Karen and find links to video tutorials for her Sizzix pop-up dies on her blog: I am not left-handed.

name: KI Memories
description: A proud member of the Hampton Art family, KI Memories has been designing happy and fun scrapbooking products since 2001. As an innovator in creativity, the company designs and manufactures decorative papers, stickers, stamps, embellishments and albums for scrapbook enthusiasts worldwide. Their colorful modern appeal and sleek style are now perfectly paired with a magical collection of dies, stamps and embossing folders for Sizzix.

name: Kid Giddy
description: Kerry Goulder has been sewing for fun since she can remember. After a sculpture class in college, a wedding and two children, Kerry began designing many unique patterns under her Kid Giddy® label, and wrote her first book, Sewing Tales to Stitch and Love: 18 Toy Patterns for the Storytelling Sewist, with F+W Media. Kerry's company motto is to "add more giddy to your life." This is a constant reminder to have fun and to do things that make you happy, which, of course, means more sewing. Kerry lives in Southern Maine with her husband and their two daughters. When she's not sewing, she loves to run and is training for her second degree black belt in Shaolin Kempo Karate. You can learn more about Kerry and see what she's up to at kidgiddy.blogspot.com

name: Kristen Adams
description: You've got a style of your own. And so does Kristen Adams. Check out her die designs shown below. Just imagine the kinds of things you could create with these designs. Then wonder how you lived without them this long.

description: You've got a style of your own. And so does Kristi Dailey. Check out her die designs shown below. Just imagine the kinds of things you could create with these designs. Then wonder how you lived without them this long.

name: Laura Kelly
description: With a creative appeal that parents and educators are sure to appreciate, Laura Kelly's exciting new designs bring more creativity to the classroom. Laura has a lifelong background in elementary education with many years of working with students of all ages. Her designs are simple, yet stellar, with a bright and whimsical quality to inspire the creative spirit and foster learning that makes a difference. To learn more about Laura, visit her website: laurakellydesigns.com.

name: Leere' Aldrich
description: You've got a style of your own. And so does Leere' Aldrich. Check out her embossing folder designs shown below. Just imagine the kinds of things you could create with these designs. Then wonder how you lived without them this long.

name: Lori Bergmann
description: You've got a style of your own. And so does Lori Bergmann. Check out her die designs shown below. Just imagine the kinds of things you could create with these designs. Then wonder how you lived without them this long.

name: Lori Whitlock
description: After several years of working in a design studio, Lori found her true passion developing products for the crafting industry. Over the past 10 years, Lori has designed for many prominent companies in our industry. Lori currently licenses paper designs and fabric, as well as digital cutting files and scrapbooking files. Sizzix proudly welcomes Lori as a licensed designer for its brand new assortment of designs to enhance cardmaking, scrapbooking, home décor and other handmade crafts. With many practical and dimensional base dies at its core, the collection offers unlimited embellishing possibilities with her paper, fabric or other material. You can learn more about Lori and see what she's up to at www.loriwhitlock.com.

name: Lynda Kanase
description: When Lynda isn't designing packaging for Sizzix as a Senior Graphic Designer she can be found in her studio repurposing her stash of flea market treasures. Having crafted all of her life, she has tried everything from silk painting to wood carving and has been scrapbooking since 1988. Always open to new discoveries, she also blogs about her crafting and flea market adventures. Her design career includes packaging, advertising and magazine design for large companies but her passion has always been crafting. It was true serendipity when she came to Sizzix. And when she isn't designing, crafting or blogging, she and her boyfriend can be found in pit row supporting her son as he furthers his professional racing career.

name: Marie Cole
description: You've got a style of your own. And so does Marie Cole. Check out her die and embossing designs shown below. Just imagine the kinds of things you could create with these designs. Then wonder how you lived without them this long.

name: Marisa Pawelko
description:
She's everything from a craft author and an industry spokesperson to a trendsetter and a sought-after personality. She's been featured on numerous TV shows and in magazines. Meet award-winning celebrity crafter, Marisa Pawelko, author of the groundbreaking how-to craft book Crazy Cool Duct Tape Projects.

Marisa is everywhere these days - serving as spokesperson for Westcott Brand® and TapeCrafters.com® as well as brand ambassador for Duck Brand® duct tape and Rowlux® Illusion Film. Now Marisa brings her unique enthusiasm to Sizzix for one-of-a-kind jewelry, fashion, locker art, home décor and more!

name: me & my BIG ideas
description: You've got a style of your own. And so does me & my BIG ideas. Check out all their die, embossing folder and texture plate designs shown below. Just imagine the kinds of things you could create with these designs. Then wonder how you lived without them this long.

name: Missouri Star Quilt Co
description: Starting small and aiming high, the family-owned Missouri Star Quilt Company began in November 2008, selling a few quilting supplies and offering machine quilting services from its Hamilton, MO store. The decision was made to grow the business online with web-based tutorials for beginning and advanced quilters. It wasn't long before Missouri Star became the biggest quilting channel on YouTube and began offering pre-cut fabrics as its core product. These stylish bundles, cut in various shapes and sizes and in an array of coordinating prints from designer fabric lines, grew the business exponentially. In less than four years, Missouri Star has been able to offer the world's largest selection of pre-cut fabrics and is a natural choice for its own line of Sizzix dies.

name: Nel Whatmore
description: Well known for her floral and abstract creations Nel is an exceptional expressionist painter with a loyal following and many collectors worldwide. She loves to explore different mediums and their ability to convey emotion. Her beautiful ranges are licensed by many companies all over the world. Producing textile designs has introduced her to the stitching and quilting world, a whole new area that continues to fascinate her. Having already designed several classic collections for fabric, she remains inspired and devoted to create more lovely new patterns. Her ultimate joy is seeing how people express themselves using her work.

name: Noralee Peterson
description: You've got a style of your own. And so does Noralee Peterson. Check out her die designs shown below. Just imagine the kinds of things you could create with these designs. Then wonder how you lived without them this long.

name: Paula Pascual
description: As a teenager in her native Spain, Paula ambitiously made cards and crafts. Starting in 2003, her experience grew as a craft store demonstrator and as a freelance creative designer/tutor. Not long after, Paula began using Sizzix products in her workshops and demonstrations. Over the last six years, Paula has been featured in popular publications such as Cardmaking and Papercraft and Crafts Beautiful. She has also authored two craft books: Creative Card Making and Handmade Celtic Cards. In addition, she has appeared several times on QVC as their craft expert. Paula enjoys working with paper, graphic design, photography and storage, which inspired her to create the Crafty Storage, a collaborative blog dedicated to storage ideas from and for all crafters.

name: Pebbles Inc
description: You've got a style of your own. And so does Pebbles Inc. Check out their die designs shown below. Just imagine the kinds of things you could create with these designs. Then wonder how you lived without them this long.

name: Pete Hughes
description:
For over ten years, Pete has been inspiring UK and European crafters with his amazing ideas. After leaving school, Pete trained as an illustrator, specializing in cartoons and caricatures before taking up a position for an educational publishing company. Pete has worked for Ellison since 2005, where he enjoys producing projects for UK and European magazines, trade shows and demonstrations. Pete is also featured regularly on television demonstrating Sizzix products, most recently on QVC. Says Pete, "My inspiration comes mainly from our wonderful customers."

Pete lives in the picturesque town of Llangollen in North Wales with his wife and two children. In his spare time, Pete helps out at his local karate club, plays and collects electric guitars and follows his beloved Liverpool Football Club.

name: Prima Marketing Inc
description: As scrapbooking evolves and changes into an exciting art form, Prima, the established leader in flower embellishments, always offers the most exciting and innovative floral-themed products to craft retailers worldwide. Together with Sizzix, this company introduces artisans and crafters alike to the newest and most original styles for scrapbook embellishments. Discover many powerful possibilities from Prima Marketing Inc.

name: Rachael Bright
description:
Rachael has loved art & design for as far back as she can remember. Born and raised in Southern California, Rachael grew up on the beach, sailing back and forth from Catalina Island. She has a passion for animals and says they seem to find her "like Ace Ventura" if they need help or a home. She loves hiking with friends and spending time with her dish-washing, rescue dog, Lily. She loves to travel (nine countries and counting!) and lived, worked and went to college in Paris, France.

Rachael says, "I just love my job as a Sizzix designer and working in such a creative atmosphere. It's a dream come true for me and I hope our customers feel that 'Joi de Vivre' when they use my designs."

name: Renee Villalobos-Campa
description: You've got a style of your own. And so does Renee Villalobos-Campa. Check out her die designs shown below. Just imagine the kinds of things you could create with these designs. Then wonder how you lived without them this long.

name: rob and bob studio
description: You've got a style of your own. And so does rob and bob studio. Check out all their die designs shown below. Just imagine the kinds of things you could create with these designs. Then wonder how you lived without them this long.

name: Rory Newell
description: You've got a style of your own. And so does Rory Newell. Check out all his latest and greatest designs shown below. Just imagine the kinds of things you could create with these designs. Then wonder how you lived without them this long.

name: Scrappy Cat
description: Scrappy Cat is an internationally recognized brand in the scrapbooking and paper crafting industry. Founded in 2003 by Kim Roberto, the company debuted its products in February of 2004 at the HIA Show (now called CHA) in Dallas, Texas, and was immediately recognized by Creating Keepsakes Magazine with a 2004 New Product(s) Editor's Choice Award. Known for its highly innovative stamp designs, stylish patterns and coordinating products, Scrappy Cat products are distributed by Darice, Inc., a proven leader in the craft market worldwide. Scrappy Cat is also a licensed designer and brand that collaborates with Sizzix (Ellison) on a wide variety of artistic die designs for the Sizzix lineup of die-cutting machines.

name: Sharyn Sowell
description: Mixed-media artist Sharyn Sowell is a true artisan who combines her hand-cut paper creations with watercolor, calligraphy and typography. Sharyn designs everything from home décor and garden products to giftware, fabric, stationery products and more for an impressive list of companies. Author of two popular craft books, she has won multiple LOUIE Awards, the Oscars® of the greeting card industry. Sharyn's original art can be seen in the British National Portrait Gallery, Children's Hospital Los Angeles and the Waldorf Astoria® Orlando. Sharyn has designed for companies like Hallmark®, Creative Converting® and York® Wallcoverings. Now her beloved art is available as Sizzix eshape Store downloadable files and as Sizzix dies and embossing folders.

name: Shelli Signature
description: You've got a style of your own. And so does Shelli Signature. Check out all her latest and greatest die and texture plate designs shown below. Just imagine the kinds of things you could create with these designs. Then wonder how you lived without them this long.

name: Stampin' Up!
description: You've got a style of your own. And so does Stampin' Up!. Check out all their latest and greatest die, embossing folder, letterpress plate and texture plate designs shown below. Just imagine the kinds of things you could create with these designs. Then wonder how you lived without them this long.

name: Stephanie Ackerman
description: Whether it's paper, fabric, dough or paint, Stephanie Ackerman is a mixed media artist and teacher who's a lot like you, combining a busy mom lifestyle with her many creative passions. Stephanie draws upon her vast experiences in stamp carving, stitching, art journaling, making tags and working with canvas and wood to inspire this uniquely upbeat collection just for you! Learn more about Stephanie by visiting her website: StephanieAckermanDesigns.com.

name: Stephanie Barnard
description: If it's possible to live, breathe, eat and sleep scrapbooking and stamping, Stephanie Barnard is giving it her best shot. Besides serving as the Sizzix spokesperson, she also offers the company's research and development team invaluable insights into new products from the crafter's perspective. She is also a licensed designer and the inspiration behind her own line of creative products for Sizzix. Stephanie is the owner and designer of a clear stamp company, The Stamps of Life. Their stamps are proudly manufactured in the USA. In addition, she is a highly sought-after teacher and demonstrator and has appeared on numerous television shows with her work included in many books, magazines and websites.

name: Stu Kilgour
description:
Stu has been in the commercial art business for 10 years, doing everything from T-shirt and storyboard design to web design and corporate identity. Stu has been with Ellison for over 5 years and has become a utility man who can do any style for any medium, often processing other artist's work and teaming with R & D on product development when not crafting his own designs for Ellison.

On a personal note, Stu works from his home in Tennessee where he spends time with his wife Lisa and their five kids. Stu loves rain, rock & roll and video games. He is currently taking correspondence courses toward a degree in Communications/Game Art.

name: Susan Tierney-Cockburn
description: Susan has taken a lifetime of creative experiences and turned them into a full-time passion. Whether it's gardening, painting, baking, and, of course, crafting, she has done it all in her own unmistakable style. Loving to share this information with others, she has taught cake decorating and bread baking. Her stamping and papercrafts - with a special emphasis on making realistic paper flowers - have lead to designing for publications and writing books. In addition, she has a blog dedicated to baking. Susan teams with Sizzix for a charming crop of products to create incredible floral designs for embellishing cards, scrapbooks or any other craft project.

name: Tim Holtz
description: Tim Holtz is the Creative Director for Ranger Industries, one of the leading manufacturers of innovative inks, paints and embossing products. Tim plays an integral part in the development and design of cutting-edge papercrafting products. Tim has teamed up with various key companies like Ranger, Advantus, Tonic Studios, Sizzix and Stampers Anonymous to bring unique products that work hand in hand with Ranger's extensive lines. Learn more about Tim and connect to video tutorials and his blog at TimHoltz.com.

name: Victoria Findlay Wolfe Quilts
description: Whether it's painting, sculpting or photography, Victoria has always been creating. But it was through her grandmother, Elda Wolfe, a "crazy quilter" whose patterns were ahead of their time, that she found the inspiration to take up quilting. Victoria's series of Double Wedding Ring quilts are based on happy childhood memories with her grandparents. Victoria is also a teacher, lecturer, fabric and thread designer, blogger and author of the popular quilting books, 15 Minutes of Play and Double Wedding Rings - Traditions Made Modern. Victoria finds that making and giving quilts in her community quilt program, along with her loving family, to be her greatest joys in life.

name: Vintaj
description: Vintaj® was founded by three women who share a passion for designing jewelry. Together, they have created a unique product to inspire all. Opening the door to endless possibilities, their naturally beautiful brass findings are hand finished and made in the USA. In 2011, Vintaj partnered with Sizzix to create beautiful dies for embossing and etching metal. This perfect pairing allows you to create personalized jewelry that is truly a one-of-a-kind expression.

name: Westminster Fibers
description: Throughout the early 1980s, Westminster Gallery owners Ken and June Bridgewater imported original knitted garments from a young American living abroad named Kaffe Fassett. Kaffe collaborated with Rowan Yarns, a fledgling yarn company in the West Yorkshire region of England and he began designing garments and yarns under his name. Kaffe suggested that Rowan team with the Bridgewaters to distribute the yarns in the American market and Westminster Fibers was born. Westminster Fibers continued to grow, becoming one of the most respected yarn companies in the hand-knitting yarn marketplace and eventually expanded into printed fabrics. With a wide assortment of fabrics, yarns and needlework kits plus many brand distributorships, Westminster Fibers offers tremendous value to every quilting or needleart enthusiast.

name: Where Women Cook
description: Where Women Cook is a quarterly magazine created by its inspiring Editor-in Chief, Jo Packham, who is also the driving force behind Where Women Create, the popular quarterly magazine that explores the creativity behind inspirational work spaces. Where Women Cook celebrates extraordinary women who are passionate about their kitchens and all things food. Whether its culinary décor, entertaining ideas or mouth-watering food and drink recipes, Where Women Cook is a welcome spice to life. And now with the Where Women Cook design collection for Sizzix, you can complement your cooking with delicious designs that any taste can appreciate.

name: Where Women Create
description: Launched in 2009, Where Women Create is the popular quarterly magazine that explores the creativity behind the inspirational work spaces and unique organizational systems of extraordinary women. Through stunning photography and inspirational stories, each issue of this quarterly magazine promises to nourish souls and motivate creative processes. The magazine is one of three top-selling magazines from its inspiring creator and Editor-in-Chief, Jo Packham. As with Where Women Create, Jo's other magazines, Where Women Cook and Where Women Do Business, tell the stories of women, written in their own words, who passionately dedicate themselves to all things handmade, food and business. And now with the Where Women Create design collection for Sizzix, you can complement your creative spaces with your own unique expressions.

name: Wordsworth
description: You've got a style of your own. And so does Wordsworth. Check out their die and embossing folder designs shown below. Just imagine the kinds of things you could create with these designs. Then wonder how you lived without them this long.

name: AllStar
description: Looking for your next AllStar® in the classroom? Look no further than the AllStar brand of machines from Ellison®. All-affordable and all-around performers, they create powerful combinations of reinforcing visuals and hands-on activities to help address your important curriculum and standards.

name: Big Shot
description:
There's a reason why we call our shape-cutting and embossing machine a Big Shot™. It's because the ever-versatile Big Shot works with the entire Sizzix® product library (with the exception of Bigz™ Plus and Bigz Pro dies) - and that includes our smallest dies to our big 6" wide plastic-backed treasures and embossing tools.

If that wasn't big enough, this portable roller machine cuts and embosses many different materials. Create your own one-of-a-kind cards, invitations, scrapbook pages, home décor, fashion, altered art, quilting and much more! (To ensure compatibility, always check accessory requirements. Machine accessories may be sold separately.)

name: Big Shot Express
description:
With just the push of a button, the Big Shot™ Express leaves the crank behind. Instead, the motorized Big Shot Express works with the entire Sizzix® product library (with the exception of Bigz™ Plus and Bigz Pro dies) - and that includes our smallest dies to our big 6" wide plastic-backed treasures and embossing tools.

If that wasn't big enough, this portable roller machine cuts and embosses many different materials. Create your own one-of-a-kind cards, invitations, scrapbook pages, home décor, fashion, altered art, quilting and much more! (To ensure compatibility, always check machine and accessory requirements. Machine accessories may be sold separately.)

name: Big Shot Plus
description:
One shape-cutting machine does it all! The Sizzix® Big Shot™ Plus Machine works with any Sizzix die or embossing folder up to 9" wide to create an amazing assortment of craft shapes.

If that wasn't enough, this powerful roller machine cuts and embosses many different materials. Create your own one-of-a-kind cards, invitations, scrapbook pages, home décor, fashion, altered art, quilting and much more using your favorite 8 1/2" x 11" materials! (To ensure compatibility, always check machine and accessory requirements. Machine accessories may be sold separately.)

name: Big Shot Pro
description:
One shape-cutting machine does it all! The Sizzix® Big Shot™ Pro Machine works with any Sizzix die or embossing folder to create an amazing assortment of craft shapes. For added versatility, these machines are compatible with SureCut™ dies from our Ellison® education brand, plus most other brands of steel-rule dies.

If that wasn't enough, this industrial strength roller machine cuts and embosses many different materials. Create your own one-of-a-kind cards, invitations, scrapbook pages, home décor, fashion, altered art, quilting and much more! (To ensure compatibility, always check machine and accessory requirements. Machine accessories may be sold separately.)

name: BIGkick
description:
Give a great BIGkick™ to your creativity! The BIGkick works with the entire Sizzix® product library (with the exception of Bigz™ Plus and Bigz Pro dies) - and that includes our smallest dies to our big 6" wide plastic-backed treasures and embossing tools.

If that wasn't big enough, this portable roller machine cuts and embosses many different materials. Create your own one-of-a-kind cards, invitations, scrapbook pages, home décor, fashion, altered art, quilting and much more! (To ensure compatibility, always check accessory requirements. Machine accessories may be sold separately.)

name: eclips
description:
Take a look at a total eclips®! The eclips is the first electronic shape-cutting machine to combine the creativity of Sizzix® artwork with amazing cutting, scoring and drawing precision and remote-controlled intelligence. This machine creates completely customizable shapes and letters to make cards, envelopes, scrapbook pages, bags, boxes, home décor projects, fashion accessories, altered art and much more!

With the Stamp2Cut™ cartridges, you can cut around Tim Holtz® Stampers Anonymous stamps. Another creative option is eCAL software which works with your computer to create and modify your own designs and then works with the eclips to cut, score or draw the shapes.

name: eclips2
description:
With no cartridges required, the newly redesigned eclips®2 DIY Electronic Cutter contains an enhanced motor with industrial-strength gears for speed, reduced noise, efficiency, precision cutting and more. In addition, the eclips2 is accompanied by free eCAL lite software to create your own designs, plus cut, score and draw/edit unique shapes for beautiful customized projects from the start.

With the eclips2 and eCAL lite, you can weld multiple shapes and letters into one cut. Use Appearance Styles, like Shadow and Blackout, to quickly change the look of letters and shapes. You can also access TrueType, OpenType and fonts currently installed on your computer, including Dingbat/Wingding fonts.

name: fabi
description:
The fabi™ Machine fabulously cuts many stylish fabric shapes to please quilters and sewers alike. The fabi is compatible with the entire Sizzix® product library (with the exception of Bigz™ Plus and Bigz Pro dies) - and that includes our smallest dies to our big 6" wide steel-rule dies and embossing tools.

If that wasn't big enough, this portable roller machine cuts a wide range of materials - everything from cardstock to leather including cotton, batting, flannel, wool and much more. With the fabi, charming shapes can be easily created for appliqué, home décor, fashion, quilting and many more crafts. (To ensure compatibility, always check accessory requirements.)

name: LetterMachine Original
description: Retired but not forgotten, Ellison® continues to support these machines with replacement parts and an ever-growing library of SureCut™ and ClearCrop™ Dies and lessons. Use Ellison shape-cutting equipment to create powerful combinations of reinforcing visuals and hands-on applications to help address your important curriculum and standards.

name: LetterMachine XL
description: Retired but not forgotten, Ellison® continues to support these machines with replacement parts and an ever-growing library of SureCut™ and ClearCrop™ Dies and lessons. Use Ellison shape-cutting equipment to create powerful combinations of reinforcing visuals and hands-on applications to help address your important curriculum and standards.

name: Original
description:
Get ready to be impressed! Our popular press-style machine cuts and embosses with absolute ease.

Along with our Originals™ dies, the original Sizzix® Machine cuts and embosses unforgettable shapes that beautifully embellish cards, scrapbook pages, papercrafts and even clothes!

Add a Sizzix System Converter and elegantly emboss with Simple Impressions® Embossing Folders or cut smaller-sized detailed designs with a mind-boggling selection of Sizzlits® dies that easily cut through cardstock, metallic foil, paper or vellum.

name: Prestige Pro
description: Up to your most pressing challenges, Prestige™ machines cut many different materials and thicknesses using Ellison® SureCut™ and ClearCrop™ Dies. Add an optional Adapter Pad and ensure compatibility with AllStar Dies and other brands' steel-rule dies, as well as Sizzix® Originals™ and Bigz™ Dies. Perfect for any library, teacher's lounge or media center, Prestige machines offer many years of high-volume shape-cutting fun to benefit any school, while supporting staff lessons and enhancing many learning activities.

name: Prestige Select
description: Up to your most pressing challenges, Prestige™ machines cut many different materials and thicknesses using Ellison® SureCut™ and ClearCrop™ Dies. Perfect for any library, teacher's lounge or media center, Prestige machines offer many years of high-volume shape-cutting fun to benefit any school, while supporting staff lessons and enhancing many learning activities.

name: Prestige SpaceSaver
description: Up to your most pressing challenges, Prestige™ machines cut many different materials and thicknesses using Ellison® SureCut™ and ClearCrop™ Dies. Perfect for any library, teacher's lounge or media center, Prestige machines offer many years of high-volume shape-cutting fun to benefit any school, while supporting staff lessons and enhancing many learning activities.

name: RollModel
description: It's our most compatible machine yet! To complement our patented line of die-cut machines, the RollModel™ uses a crank handle to accommodate all Ellison® SureCut™ and ClearCrop™ Dies, as well as AllStar® Dies through its extra wide opening. The results are instant, curriculum-based applications to enhance any subject, lesson or learning environment.

name: Sidekick
description:
With a few turns of its handle, the Sidekick® cuts single sheets of lightweight paper to cardstock and transforms them into something special. The Sidekick works with the entire Sizzix® Sizzlits® product library (with the exception of large Sizzlits dies) - and that includes our small dies to our 12" long Sizzlits Decorative Strip dies.

If that wasn't impressive enough, the portable, affordable and adorable roller machine also elegantly embosses with Textured Impressions embossing folders (small only). The handy vacuum seal attaches to most work surfaces for creativity anywhere. Create your own one-of-a-kind cards, invitations, scrapbook pages and much more! (To ensure compatibility, always check machine and accessory requirements.)

name: SophistiCut
description: Easy and elegant, the Sizzix® SophistiCut™ Die-Cutting Machine sports a stylish purse design with a 3" wide opening to accommodate small, medium and border-sized Sizzix Originals™ dies. The machine cuts a wide range of materials - everything from cardstock to fabric. The SophistiCut features a fold-out working platform, durable rollers and a large, easy-to-turn side handle. With the SophistiCut, charming shapes can be easily created for appliqué, home décor, fashion, jewelry, altered art, cardmaking, scrapbooking and many more crafts. (To ensure compatibility, always check accessory requirements.)

name: SuperStar
description: Looking for your next AllStar® in the classroom? Look no further than the AllStar brand of machines from Ellison®. All-affordable and all-around performers, they create powerful combinations of reinforcing visuals and hands-on activities to help address your important curriculum and standards.

name: Ellison SuperStar Excel Machine
description: For today's creative classroom, the pro-strength SuperStar™ Excel Machine easily cuts a wide variety of materials to create memorable lessons, study aids, activities and decorations. With just a few turns of its ergonomic handle, the SuperStar Excel Machine uses an extra-wide roller to accommodate SureCut™ and ClearCrop™ Dies through its 12"-wide opening. The included Extended Sliding Tray easily moves multiple dies through the machine's rollers for perfectly cut shapes every time. By using the included Sliding Adapter Pad, you can also cut with Sizzix® Originals™ and Bigz™ Dies and Ellison® AllStar® Dies as well as other brands' steel-rule dies.
